{
  "text": "However, we surmise that 2,400 IU daily may not be sufficient based on the results of several studies-albeit those studies used different regimens of vitamin D 2 or vitamin D 3 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] -and the Endocrine Society guidelines that recommend initial treatment of vitamin D deficient adults with vitamin D 2 or vitamin D 3 doses of 50,000 IU once a week or 6000 IU per day to achieve a blood concentration of 25(OH)D above 30.0 ng/mL [CITATION_3] .",
